## Current Focus

- Keep the maintained package small: `data`, `anonymization`, `linkage`,
  `recommender`, `reporting`, and `cli`.
- Prefer improving the synthetic demo and final report over adding new modules.
- Treat old notebooks as historical unless a piece is deliberately promoted
  into `src/guardrails_sensitive_data`.

## Later, If Needed

- Add confidence intervals across multiple seeds.
- Promote the Spark ALS notebook into the package only if the lightweight bias
  recommender is no longer enough.
- If runtime IMDb scraping proves brittle, add a small documented cache-refresh
  workflow that writes reviewed scrape outputs back to `notebooks/imdb_data.csv`.
